[The wild boar is an invasive species in Argentina. In endemic areas of trichinellosis, the wild animals that are known to play a role in the maintenance of _Trichinella_ spp. are rats, wild boars (both introduced species), armadillos, and pumas. Wild boars and armadillos are used as a source of animal protein. - Mod.PMB

